
**Project Title: Hall of the World’s Most Useless Superpowers**

Project overview:- It’s a fun platform where people can log in and create their own lists of the most ridiculously useless superpowers they can imagine. Users can rate how useless these powers are, share their lists, and see what others have come up with.

Key features:-

Personalized Lists: Each user gets their own list of superpowers to manage.

Rate and Rank: Users can rank superpowers on a "Uselessness Scale" and see how their favorites compare.

Leaderboards: A global leaderboard highlights the most useless superpower submissions of all time.

Dynamic Dashboard: The dashboard is super simple to navigate, so you can easily add, edit, or just browse through your favorite superpowers.

Fun Insights: You’ll get insights like which powers are the most popular and which one holds the title of “Ultimate Useless Superpower.”

Tech Stack:
Frontend: React.js , css framework
Backend: Node.js, Express.js and MongoDB

Why This Project: I’ll get to practice building a full-stack application, handling user-specific data, and creating a fun, engaging experience for everyone who uses it.


